# Suricata IDS/IPS Deployment

## Objective
Deploy Suricata IDS functionality on OPNsense and validate custom intrusion detection rules using simulated Nmap reconnaissance traffic.

## Configuration Summary
- Enabled Intrusion Detection features in OPNsense
- Configured Suricata rule management
- Hosted custom rules through Python HTTP server on Kali Linux
- Imported external custom ruleset into OPNsense
- Enabled custom ruleset within Intrusion Detection administration

## Custom Rule Validation
Initial rule deployment failed to generate alerts due to:
- Incorrect XML structure
- Inconsistent rule naming
- Invalid subnet targeting
- Old rule conflicts remaining in OPNsense

## Corrective Actions
- Removed old conflicting rule and XML files
- Renamed rules consistently
- Corrected XML formatting
- Corrected subnet definition from host notation to network notation
- Re-imported and re-enabled ruleset
- Restarted Intrusion Detection service

## Final Working Rule
The final Suricata rule successfully detected SYN scan activity generated from Kali Linux using Nmap.

## Validation Testing
Nmap scan used:
nmap -sS -Pn --top-ports 500 10.200.200.254

## Result
Suricata successfully generated intrusion detection alerts within OPNsense alert monitoring interface.
